cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the optimization of crowdsourced human computation, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also involves analyzing the stochastic behavior of human workers, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for performance optimization, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the experiments conducted on Amazon Mechanical Turk involve social and information networks (cs.SI).
